text: Depression, anxiety, bipolar, and trauma have governed every aspect of my life fo as long as I can remember. I have had multiple suicide attempts, rehab, every antidepressant known to man, and nothing has ever gotten better. I am currently on medical leave from my last suicide attempt. No one in my life knows, I just pretend to go to work everyday.But now I am finally at peace. I am going to see my all-time favorite band in NYC soon, see the sights, and go to restaurants I have been wanting to try for years. I will not be coming back. I have tried to end it before but this time its different; I feel at peace. I am able to go out on my terms while crossing stuff off my bucket list (rather than the usual abstaining because I am paralyzed by anxiety). This last month since I have made this decision has been the best in 9+ years. I am not sure why I am posting this other than to put something of myself out into the ether, I guess in a vain attempt to avoid being completely forgotten. Thank you all.
